<p><a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/technology/gadgetbox/update-your-iphone-now-fix-passcode-vulnerability-1C8932493"><img align="left" border="0" src="http://msnbcmedia.msn.com/j/MSNBC/Components/Photo/_new/1c6525227-121012-5c1c4252499-screen-shot-2012-10-12-11-42.thumb.jpeg" alt="Anyone — with some practice, and really great timing — can bypass your iPhone's passcode in order to make calls, send out emails and messages, scroll through call histories, view contacts and more, thanks to a security flaw in the iOS operating system." style="margin:0 5px 5px 0" /></a>Anyone — with some practice, and really great timing — can bypass your iPhone's passcode in order to make calls, send out emails and messages, scroll through call histories, view contacts and more, thanks to a security flaw in the iOS operating system.</p><br clear="all" />
